{
  "text": "Major depressive disorder (MDD) is a globally prevalent psychi atric disorder causing a great social burden. In hopes of identifying better treatment options, many attempts have been made to clarify pathological brain mechanisms. Using novel imaging techniques in vivo, several microstructural brain abnormalities have been reported. [CITATION_1] It is likely that most psychiatric disorders do not result from a deficit in a single brain area and that a network perspective is necessary to explain their complex etiology. Accordingly, studies of both functional and structural connectivity have become popular.",
